The paper discusses the use of knowledge graphs and natural language processing for context mining and knowledge discovery in the life sciences domain. This falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of text mining and language data, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of graph queries and the graph-theoretic foundation of the approach suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
